<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>The Masters Tournament, also known as The Masters, or The U.S. Masters outside of the United States, is one of the four major championships in professional golf. Scheduled for the first full week of April, it is the first of the majors to be played each year. Unlike the other major championships, the Masters is held each year at the same location, Augusta National Golf Club, a private golf club in the city of Augusta, Georgia, USA. The Masters was started by Clifford Roberts and Bobby Jones, who designed Augusta National with course architect Alister MacKenzie. The tournament is an official money event on the PGA Tour, the PGA European Tour, and the Japan Golf Tour. The field of players is smaller than those of the other major championships because it is an invitational event, entry being controlled by the Augusta National Golf Club.
                  <br><br>The tournament has a number of traditions. A green jacket is awarded to the winner of each tournament, which must be returned to the clubhouse after a year. The Champions dinner, inaugurated by Ben Hogan, is held on the Tuesday before each tournament, and is only open to past champions and certain board members of the Augusta National Golf Club. Beginning in 1963, legendary golfers, usually past champions, have hit an honorary tee shot on the morning of the first round. Such golfers have included Sam Snead, Byron Nelson, and Arnold Palmer, who has hit the tee shot the last two years. Since 1960, a semi-social Par 3 Contest, on a par-3 course on Augusta National's grounds, has been played on the day before the first round of each Masters Tournament.
                  <br><br>Masters: Shin Harukanaru Augusta is a golf game only released in Japan based on the classic U.S, tournament of golf.
                  <br><br>Top players gathered from around the world compete for one of the premier golf tournaments that takes place in the Augusta National Golf Club".
                  <br><br>The vision and immersive sound effects recreate the beautiful 18th holes. Camera-like perspective and to follow the trajectory of each ball with a single button help features and functionality set, you can experience one of the most prestigious courses in the world in vivid detail the background color is represented.
                  <br><br>Up to four human players can play at the same time in this recreation of the Augusta national club.
                  <br><br>The player uses the Augusta National Golf Club course, in different play modes (Stroke Play, Match Play, Tournament, and Masters Tournament). Each hole has an opening fly over with descriptive text in Japanese.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>One of the most prestigious courses in the world "Augusta National Golf Club" enjoy a 3D golf game set in the tournament. 18 holes Strategic immersive 3D video reproduction. Camera uses a ball to follow the trajectory of a fly ball on the back also has a variety of features tailored to help and one place to another button.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Golf theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

